<sect1 id="zend.date.overview">
    <title>Zend_Date API Overview</title>
    <para>
        While the <code>Zend_Date</code> API remains simplistic and unitary it is very rich
        and mighty.
    </para>
    <para>
        The following overview should provide help to the functions.
    </para>
    <sect2 id="zend.date.overview.general">
        <title>General Functions</title>
        <para>
            The general functions expect a constant providing the date's desired part
            (such as Zend_Date::HOUR). Those constants are valid to all functions. A 
            list of all available constants is provided in <xref linkend="zend.date.constants" />
        </para>
        <para>
            The following general functions will be available:
        </para>
        <table>
            <title>General functions</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Function</entry>
                        <entry>Description</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>get()</entry>
                        <entry>date output</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>set()</entry>
                        <entry>date input</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>add()</entry>
                        <entry>adding with dates</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>sub()</entry>
                        <entry>subtraction with dates</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>copy()</entry>
                        <entry>copy a date and return a new object</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>compare()</entry>
                        <entry>compares dates by time. returns 0, 1 or -1</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>equals()</entry>
                        <entry>compares dates by equality. returns boolean</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isEarlier()</entry>
                        <entry>checks against age. returns true, if younger</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isLater()</entry>
                        <entry>checks against age. returns true, if older</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </sect2>
    <sect2 id="zend.date.overview.detail">
        <title>Detailed functions</title>
        <para>
            The detailed functions do not need constants, but are to use only for a specified part
            of the date. There are lots of them, but because of their intuitiveness their are easy
            to guess. Not all possible variants will be supported.
        </para>
        <para>
            The following detailed functions are available:
        </para>
        <table>
            <title>Detailed functions</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Related</entry>
                        <entry>Output</entry>
                        <entry>Seting</entry>
                        <entry>Addition</entry>
                        <entry>Subtraction</entry>
                        <entry>Comparation</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Unix Timestamp</entry>
                        <entry>getTimestamp()</entry>
                        <entry>setTimestamp()</entry>
                        <entry>addTimestamp()</entry>
                        <entry>subTimestamp()</entry>
                        <entry>compareTimestamp()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Date</entry>
                        <entry>getDate()</entry>
                        <entry>setDate()</entry>
                        <entry>addDate()</entry>
                        <entry>subDate()</entry>
                        <entry>compareDate()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Time</entry>
                        <entry>getTime()</entry>
                        <entry>setTime()</entry>
                        <entry>addTime()</entry>
                        <entry>subTime()</entry>
                        <entry>compareTime()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Year</entry>
                        <entry>getYear()</entry>
                        <entry>setYear()</entry>
                        <entry>addYear()</entry>
                        <entry>subYear()</entry>
                        <entry>compareYear()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Month</entry>
                        <entry>getMonth()</entry>
                        <entry>setMonth()</entry>
                        <entry>addMonth()</entry>
                        <entry>subMonth()</entry>
                        <entry>compareMonth()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Day</entry>
                        <entry>getDay()</entry>
                        <entry>setDay()</entry>
                        <entry>addDay()</entry>
                        <entry>subDay()</entry>
                        <entry>compareDay()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Weekday</entry>
                        <entry>getWeekday()</entry>
                        <entry>setWeekday()</entry>
                        <entry>addWeekday()</entry>
                        <entry>subWeekday()</entry>
                        <entry>compareWeekday()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Day of Year</entry>
                        <entry>getDayOfYear()</entry>
                        <entry>setDayOfYear()</entry>
                        <entry>addDayOfYear()</entry>
                        <entry>subDayOfYear()</entry>
                        <entry>compareDayOfYear()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Hour</entry>
                        <entry>getHour()</entry>
                        <entry>setHour()</entry>
                        <entry>addHour()</entry>
                        <entry>subHour()</entry>
                        <entry>compareHour()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Minute</entry>
                        <entry>getMinute()</entry>
                        <entry>setMinute()</entry>
                        <entry>addMinute()</entry>
                        <entry>subMinute()</entry>
                        <entry>compareMinute()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Second</entry>
                        <entry>getSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>setSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>addSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>subSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>compareSecond()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Millisecond</entry>
                        <entry>getMilliSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>setMilliSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>addMilliSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>subMilliSecond()</entry>
                        <entry>compareMilliSecond()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Week</entry>
                        <entry>getWeek()</entry>
                        <entry>setWeek()</entry>
                        <entry>addWeek()</entry>
                        <entry>subWeek()</entry>
                        <entry>compareWeek()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>ISO 8601 date</entry>
                        <entry>getIso()</entry>
                        <entry>setIso()</entry>
                        <entry>addIso()</entry>
                        <entry>subIso()</entry>
                        <entry>compareIso()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Arpa date</entry>
                        <entry>getArpa()</entry>
                        <entry>setArpa()</entry>
                        <entry>addArpa()</entry>
                        <entry>subArpa()</entry>
                        <entry>compareArpa()</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>TimeZone</entry>
                        <entry>getTimeZone()</entry>
                        <entry>setTimeZone()</entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </sect2>
    <sect2 id="zend.date.overview.others">
        <title>Additional Functions</title>
        <para>
            Certainly there are some additional functions not fitting into the above scheme while
            being helpful.
        </para>
        <para>
            The following additional functions are available:
        </para>
        <table>
            <title>Additional Functions</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Function</entry>
                        <entry>Description</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>toString()</entry>
                        <entry>Is able to return a user-defined string</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>toValue()</entry>
                        <entry>Converts a date to a digit</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>now()</entry>
                        <entry>Returns the current date</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isLeapYear()</entry>
                        <entry>Is the year a leap year?</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isToday()</entry>
                        <entry>Is the date today?</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isTomorrow()</entry>
                        <entry>Is the date tomorrow?</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>isYesterday()</entry>
                        <entry>is the date yesterday?</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>getSunRise()</entry>
                        <entry>Return the date's time of sunrise</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>getSunSet()</entry>
                        <entry>Return the date's time of sunset</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>getSunInfo()</entry>
                        <entry>Return an array with the date's sun dates</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>getFractionalPrecision()</entry>
                        <entry>Return the precision of the part seconds</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>setFractionalPrecision()</entry>
                        <entry>Set the precision of the part seconds</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </sect2>
    <sect2 id="zend.date.overview.addons">
        <title>Additional Information</title>
        <para>
            A list of time constants is provided in <xref linkend="zend.date.constants" />
        </para>
        <para>
            <link linkend="zend.date.constants.list">Constants for general functions</link>
        </para>
        <para>
            A list of string constants is provided in <xref linked="zend.date.constants" />
        </para>
        <para>
            <link linkend="zend.date.constants.format">Constants for string output functions</link>
        </para>
    </sect2>
</sect1>
